From 9999999999990000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kairo POC <kairo-poc@local>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 15:25:00 -0700
Subject: [RFC/POC PATCH 9/9] block: align Kairo sysfs counters with foundation stack

Subsystem touched:
- `block/mq-deadline.c`

New Kairo concept:
- one aligned sysfs counter set for the foundation layer, including merge
  instrumentation and request-size histogram counters

Relation to AI KV-cache traffic:
- the benchmark must prove whether decode, prefetch, prefill, eviction, and
  hinted-request paths are active instead of treating all dispatches as generic
- merge and shape counters reveal whether KV-cache reads are fragmenting

Temporary implementation:
- keep sysfs real first and leave debugfs as a later follow-up
- merge instrumentation flags travel per-request; the scheduler accumulates
  aggregate counters at dispatch time

Still to validate:
- whether any extra counters beyond the foundation set are worth keeping
- whether the request-size histogram is better as a debugfs snapshot

diff --git a/block/mq-deadline.c b/block/mq-deadline.c
index 8b840aa..d91f31a 100644
--- a/block/mq-deadline.c
+++ b/block/mq-deadline.c
@@
